Deploy It (two clicks)
Go to the freshly created GitHub repo → Settings → Secrets → Actions
• Add one secret named TICKERS (e.g. TSLA,AMD,GME— change anytime).
Back to the repo README, you will see “Deploy to Render” button (Render is Heroku-style free hosting).
• Click → choose FREE plan → wait ~90 s.
• Render detects the render.yaml, builds both services at once (backend at https://YOUR-APP.onrender.com, frontend at https://YOUR-APP.onrender.com/static).
That’s it. No terminals, no bills, no coding knowledge.
Your personal “world-class squeeze machine” is now on the web and will refresh every 5 minutes automatically. 🎯   Changing / Adding Tickers Later
In Render dashboard → squeeze-backend → Environment → TICKERS
Edit the comma-separated list → Save → Re-deploy (one click).
